snippet.textDisplay: While I usually agree with Grace on most reviews, I mostly disagree on this one. Was it great? No. Was it good? Yes! It wrapped up the Skywalker Saga as best it could, made sense of some things shown in TLJ, had some great action sequences, and some truly heart felt moments. What stopped it from being great is that there are moments of cheese in there that could have been done better, or were completely unnecessary (like the Knights of Ren reference Grace made in the review). Ultimately though, it was satisfying to see and experience the conclusion of something that has been a part of my whole life (I was born the year A New Hope came out).

snippet.textDisplay: Regardless of what happens, or what the conversation is about the movie and the story - I am committed to saying I liked it, and praising the special effects and the score. And I'll leave it at that. I'm not even impressed by big time special effects, and don't go to see movies based on that. But story and character-wise, I checked out of this trilogy in the first 15 minutes of TFA. But, I love John Williams scores, I love the space battles, and the sprawling planet-scapes. For all I care I could go watch 2 hours of nothing but Star Wars inspired scenes with no story or characters. And that's what I'm pretending to do for this movie.
snippet.textOriginal: Regardless of what happens, or what the conversation is about the movie and the story - I am committed to saying I liked it, and praising the special effects and the score. And I'll leave it at that. I'm not even impressed by big time special effects, and don't go to see movies based on that. But story and character-wise, I checked out of this trilogy in the first 15 minutes of TFA. But, I love John Williams scores, I love the space battles, and the sprawling planet-scapes. snippet.textDisplay: I consider both the prequels and sequels to be steaming piles of shit. But the difference is that the prequel's shit, much like fertiliser, allowed for other things to grow out of it, like the excellent Clone Wars animated series and a slew of good games. It expanded the universe in a positive way, even if the execution was very poor. The sequel's shit, on the other hand, is so putrid, so acidic, so corrosive that nothing will grow out of it. It's done the opposite of fertilising; it's salted the earth so that nothing will ever grow there. There will be no positive legacy from the sequels. Disney wants these sequels to father more movies, but they've castrated themselves.
snippet.textOriginal: I consider both the prequels and sequels to be steaming piles of shit. But the difference is that the prequel's shit, much like fertiliser, allowed for other things to grow out of it, like the excellent Clone Wars animated series and a slew of good games. snippet.textDisplay: I disagree, really enjoyed the movie! People seem so eager to hate new Star Wars these days... Criticisms of pacing, and a bit too much fan service are fair. But overall considering how much they had to wrap up and course correct they did a great job! Thoroughly entertaining, bringing back the sagas best villain, amazing duels, cool twists and turns ! Was it perfect? No! Was it a bit convoluted? Yes, was it a terrible movie ? No , it’s good imo 🤷🏼‍♂️ loves that  leiyas back story fleshed our more (training) , lives kylo’s redemption, loved reys skills with the force 🔥 WISH anakin (Hayden) was in it though, very disappointing
